Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: shortfun
Version: 0.0.1
Summary: Short lambda functions for built in operations
Home-page: https://www.github.com/alrudolph/shortfun
License: MIT
Author: Alex Rudolph
Author-email: alex3rudolph@gmail.com
Requires-Python: >=3.8,<4.0
Classifier: License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License
Classifier: Programming Language :: Python :: 3
Classifier: Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10
Classifier: Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8
Classifier: Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9
Project-URL: Repository, https://www.github.com/alrudolph/shortfun
Description-Content-Type: text/markdown

```py
from shortfun import sf

>>> filtered = filter(sf.gt(10), [1, 20, 10, 8, 30])
>>> list(filtered)
[20, 30]
```

```py
from shortfun import _

>>> mapped = map(sf.add(10), [1, 20, 10, 8, 30])
>>> list(mapped)
[11, 30, 20, 18, 40]
```
Using the shorter-hand method:

```py
from shortfun import _

>>> filtered = filter(_ > 10, [1, 20, 10, 8, 30])
>>> list(filtered)
[20, 30]
```

```py
from shortfun import _

>>> mapped = map(_ + 10, [1, 20, 10, 8, 30])
>>> list(mapped)
[11, 30, 20, 18, 40]
```

